<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> Elisha Scott Loomis published over 360 proofs in his book Pythagorean Proposition (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0873530365" class="internal">ISBN 0873530365</a>).</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPhillips2009">Phillips, George (2005). <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=psFwdN6V6icC&amp;pg=PR7&amp;lpg=PR7&amp;dq=there+is+nothing+in+the+world+of+mathematics+that+corresponds+to+an+audience+in+a+concert+hall,+where+the+passive+listen+to+the+active.+Happily,+mathematicians+are+all+doers,+not+spectators.&amp;source=web&amp;ots=GBNplD5Kl9&amp;sig=k3_W0DQ5LM7UCD_6Xw7RBdYuSto&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ct=result" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=psFwdN6V6icC&amp;pg=PR7&amp;lpg=PR7&amp;dq=there+is+nothing+in+the+world+of+mathematics+that+corresponds+to+an+audience+in+a+concert+hall,+where+the+passive+listen+to+the+active.+Happily,+mathematicians+are+all+doers,+not+spectators.&amp;source=web&amp;ots=GBNplD5Kl9&amp;sig=k3_W0DQ5LM7UCD_6Xw7RBdYuSto&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ct=result" rel="nofollow">"Preface"</a>. <i>Mathematics Is Not a Spectator Sport</i>. <a href="/wiki/Springer_Science%2BBusiness_Media" title="Springer Science+Business Media">Springer Science+Business Media</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0387255281" class="internal">ISBN 0387255281</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=psFwdN6V6icC&amp;pg=PR7&amp;lpg=PR7&amp;dq=there+is+nothing+in+the+world+of+mathematics+that+corresponds+to+an+audience+in+a+concert+hall,+where+the+passive+listen+to+the+active.+Happily,+mathematicians+are+all+doers,+not+spectators.&amp;source=web&amp;ots=GBNplD5Kl9&amp;sig=k3_W0DQ5LM7UCD_6Xw7RBdYuSto&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ct=result" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=psFwdN6V6icC&amp;pg=PR7&amp;lpg=PR7&amp;dq=there+is+nothing+in+the+world+of+mathematics+that+corresponds+to+an+audience+in+a+concert+hall,+where+the+passive+listen+to+the+active.+Happily,+mathematicians+are+all+doers,+not+spectators.&amp;source=web&amp;ots=GBNplD5Kl9&amp;sig=k3_W0DQ5LM7UCD_6Xw7RBdYuSto&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ct=result" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=psFwdN6V6icC&amp;pg=PR7&amp;lpg=PR7&amp;dq=there+is+nothing+in+the+world+of+mathematics+that+corresponds+to+an+audience+in+a+concert+hall,+where+the+passive+listen+to+the+active.+Happily,+mathematicians+are+all+doers,+not+spectators.&amp;source=web&amp;ots=GBNplD5Kl9&amp;sig=k3_W0DQ5LM7UCD_6Xw7RBdYuSto&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ct=result</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-08-22</span>.  ""...there is nothing in the world of mathematics that corresponds to an audience in a concert hall, where the passive listen to the active. Happily, mathematicians are all <i>doers</i>, not spectators."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Preface&amp;rft.atitle=Mathematics+Is+Not+a+Spectator+Sport&amp;rft.aulast=Phillips&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft.au=Phillips%2C+George&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BSpringer+Science%2BBusiness+Media%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0387255281&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DpsFwdN6V6icC%26pg%3DPR7%26lpg%3DPR7%26dq%3Dthere%2Bis%2Bnothing%2Bin%2Bthe%2Bworld%2Bof%2Bmathematics%2Bthat%2Bcorresponds%2Bto%2Ban%2Baudience%2Bin%2Ba%2Bconcert%2Bhall%2C%2Bwhere%2Bthe%2Bpassive%2Blisten%2Bto%2Bthe%2Bactive.%2BHappily%2C%2Bmathematicians%2Bare%2Ball%2Bdoers%2C%2Bnot%2Bspectators.%26source%3Dweb%26ots%3DGBNplD5Kl9%26sig%3Dk3_W0DQ5LM7UCD_6Xw7RBdYuSto%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26oi%3Dbook_result%26resnum%3D1%26ct%3Dresult&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Mathematical_beauty"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Abraham_Moles" title="Abraham Moles">A. Moles</a>: <i>Théorie de l'information et perception esthétique</i>, Paris, Denoël, 1973 (<a href="/wiki/Information_Theory" title="Information Theory" class="mw-redirect">Information Theory</a> and aesthetical perception)</li>
